<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7538&amp;p=75039#p75039"><![CDATA[
I'm sure that they should always be running no matter what.  It's not like the MMC3's scanline counter that watches for the A12 line which freezes when rendering is disabled.<br /><br />Just make sure you have the even/odd prerender scanline behavior correct.<br /><br />Also, a Game Boy is actually capable of stopping the screen, unlike the NES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Mar 03, 2011 12:56 pm</p><hr />
